MPLS is a forwarding mechanism - a method of moving packets through a network using labels instead of IP addresses.

Configuring the Multi Protocol Label Switching (MPLS) on a router (which is configured on the routers inside the ISP's network):

Router(config)# ip cef
Router(config)# interface GigabitEthernet 0/0
Router(config-if)# mpls ip
Router(config-if)# exit
Router(config)# mpls label protocol ldp
Router(config)# end
Router# show mpls interfaces
Router# show mpls ldp neighbor
Router# show mpls forwarding-table

NB : LDP (Label Distribution Protocol) is the actual protocol that MPLS uses to distribute labels between routers.
